# Patch 0017 — Kavacha welcome flow (ROADMAP Phase 3: own welcome flow).
#
# Reuses Zen's excellent welcome framework (page sequencing, sidebar
# titles/buttons, spring animations, l10n) and replaces the PAGES:
#   kept    — import + set-default-browser; default search engine (both
#             vendor-neutral and genuinely useful)
#   removed — Zen's essentials picker (Zen-branded site list) and the
#             per-space gradient picker; the "zen basics" folder and
#             essential-pinning in finish() went with them
#   added   — Choose your look (Midnight default / Light / Auto ->
#             zen.view.window.scheme, applies live behind the card);
#             Pick your color (swatch grid -> zen.theme.accent-color;
#             system-accent swatch clears it; live preview via inline
#             --zen-primary-color; this is where the no-default-accent
#             decision becomes the user's choice); How should new tabs
#             open? (centered floating search vs Kavacha dashboard ->
#             zen.urlbar.replace-newtab)
# Title becomes "Welcome to / your personal internet"; the finish
# animation mark is the Kavacha branding logo instead of Zen's icon.
#
# Testing note: brand-new profiles restart once during first startup
# (add-on/langpack init), which consumes zen.welcome-screen.seen in the
# throwaway first session — pin it false in user.js when testing.
#
# Marionette-verified on a fresh profile: welcome shows naturally, all
# five pages advance, accent + scheme + newtab prefs persist, finish
# removes the overlay and restores chrome. Applies on top of 0016.
